The paper discusses two popular learning algorithms, SVMs and LMNN, and their relation from a metric learning perspective. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as well as computer vision (cs.CV) since both algorithms are commonly used in image classification tasks. Additionally, the paper's focus on metric learning could also place it in the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) since metric learning is a common technique in these fields. Finally, the paper's use of SVMs and LMNN in benchmark datasets suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
